---
id: org.dxos.plugin.crx
name: CrxPlugin
version: 0.3.0
---

Coordinates with the `@dxos/composer-crx` browser extension. Owns the Composer
side of the page-actions bridge: plugins contribute page actions (serializable
descriptor + target operation) under a plugin-scoped capability; the extension
caches the descriptors in its registry and invokes them over same-origin
`window` `CustomEvent`s. This plugin answers registry-list requests, validates
invoke requests, resolves the active space, executes the target operation, and
surfaces outcomes as toasts. It also contributes three picker actions
(Person, Organization, Note) whose operations map a page snapshot to an ECHO
object, and owns the user-facing settings surface — including the render-proxy
settings (absorbed from the retired plugin-extension) for the extension's
page-rendering facility.

The extension owns the DOM picker, popup toolbar, extractors, and bridge
sender; this plugin owns envelope validation, snapshot → ECHO object mapping,
and user feedback (toast). The extension keeps a hand-validated mirror of the
wire types at `packages/apps/composer-crx/src/page-actions/types.ts` which
must be updated in lockstep.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term   | URI                            |
|--------|--------------------------------|
| `type` | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat` | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test` | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |

## Types

```mdl
type Settings
  desc: |
    User preferences for extension ↔ Composer coordination, persisted via the
    app-framework settings store. Only user-set values are stored; defaults
    are applied by consumers when reading the atom. All fields are optional.
    The fields are a configuration surface; enforcement is owned by whichever
    consumer reads the atom.
  fields:
    enabled?: boolean             # default: true. "Accept extension actions" preference.
    autoOpenAfterClip?: boolean   # default: false. "Open after action" preference.
    renderProxyEnabled?: boolean  # default: true. "Use extension to render pages" preference.
    renderTimeout?: number        # default: 20000. Max ms to wait for a render.
    renderActiveTab?: boolean     # default: false. Render in a focused tab.
    developerMode?: boolean       # default: false. Verbose logging / previews.
```

```mdl
type Source
  fields:
    url: string
    title: string
    favicon?: string
    clippedAt: string           # ISO timestamp
```

```mdl
type Selection
  fields:
    text: string                # innerText of the picked subtree
    html?: string               # outerHTML, possibly truncated
    htmlTruncated?: boolean
    rect?: { x: number, y: number, width: number, height: number }
```

```mdl
type Hints
  desc: |
    Cheap signals harvested from the whole page at capture time. The mappings
    use a subset (h1, og:title, og:description, og:image) as fallbacks; a
    future agent stage may interpret all of them.
  fields:
    ogTitle?: string
    ogDescription?: string
    ogImage?: string
    jsonLd?: unknown[]
    h1?: string
    firstImage?: string
```

```mdl
type Snapshot
  desc: |
    Generic page capture produced by the extension's `snapshot` extractor.
    Travels as the `inputs` of an invoke request.
  fields:
    source: Source
    selection?: Selection
    hints?: Hints
    imageData?: string          # downscaled primary-image thumbnail (data URL),
                                # captured by the extension's background worker
    html?: string
    htmlTruncated?: boolean
```

```mdl
type PageActionDescriptor
  desc: |
    Serializable descriptor for a plugin-contributed page action, synced to
    the extension's registry cache. Invocation is correlated by `id`.
  fields:
    id: string                  # stable plugin-scoped action id
    label: string               # human-readable action name
    icon: string                # phosphor icon identifier
    urlPatterns: string[]       # match patterns the action applies to
    predicate?: { exists: string }  # lazy DOM condition (CSS selector)
    extractor: { name: string, params?: unknown }  # extension-bundled extractor
    contexts: string[]          # surfaces: popup | page | selection | link | picker
    operation: string           # operation key, display/diagnostics only
```

```mdl
type PageAction
  desc: |
    A live page-action contribution: the descriptor fields plus the actual
    operation definition (serialized to its key string when listed). The
    target operation must accept `{ snapshot: Snapshot, target: Database }`
    and return `{ id: string }`.
```

```mdl
type ListRequest
  desc: |
    Sent by the extension as `composer:page-actions:list`; acked as
    `composer:page-actions:list:ack`.
  fields:
    version: number             # runtime check: only 1 is supported
    id: string                  # correlation id, echoed in the ack
```

```mdl
type ListAck
  fields:
    version: number             # always 1
    id: string
    ok: boolean
    actions?: PageActionDescriptor[]  # when ok = true
    error?: string              # stable error code when ok = false
```

```mdl
type InvokeRequest
  desc: |
    Sent by the extension as `composer:page-action:invoke`; acked as
    `composer:page-action:invoke:ack`. Decoded in two passes: a loose
    envelope ({ version, id? }) first, so newer versions yield
    `unsupportedVersion` rather than the generic `invalidPayload` and
    malformed payloads can still echo the request id.
  fields:
    version: number             # runtime check: only 1 is supported
    id: string                  # correlation id, echoed in the ack
    actionId: string            # id of the registered action to invoke
    page: { url: string, title: string, favicon?: string }
    inputs: unknown             # extractor output; `snapshot` yields Snapshot
    invokedFrom: popup | contextMenu | picker
```

```mdl
type InvokeAck
  fields:
    version: number             # always 1
    id: string
    ok: boolean
    objectId?: string           # ID of the created object when ok = true
    error?: string              # stable error code when ok = false:
                                #   invalidPayload | unsupportedVersion |
                                #   unknownAction | noSpace | operationFailed
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Settings Capability

  req F-1.1:
    when: plugin is activated
    then: |
      a single `Settings` atom is registered under a plugin-scoped capability
      and contributed to `AppCapabilities.Settings` so the standard settings
      UI surfaces it.

  req F-1.2:
    when: another plugin reads the capability
    then: it receives the current Settings with defaults applied
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Settings Surface

  req F-2.1:
    when: the app-framework settings panel renders the CRX section
    then: |
      a schema-driven form is shown covering all Settings fields, wired to
      the Settings atom and persisted on change.

  req F-2.2:
    when: the user presses the Test connection button
    then: |
      a ping round-trips over the page → content-script → background path and
      reports the extension's name and version on success, or the failure
      reason otherwise.
```

```mdl
feat F-2c: Settings Enforcement

  req F-2c.1:
    when: `enabled` is false and a page-action invoke arrives
    then: |
      no object is created; the request is still acked (so the extension does
      not time out) with the stable error code `disabled`

  req F-2c.2:
    when: `autoOpenAfterClip` is true and a page action succeeds
    then: the created object is opened via LayoutOperation.Open

  req F-2c.3:
    when: `autoOpenAfterClip` is false (default)
    then: focus is not moved; only the success toast is shown
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Page Action Contributions
  desc: |
    Plugins contribute `PageAction[]` under the plugin-scoped
    `CrxCapabilities.PageAction` capability. Other plugins contribute their
    own actions the same way (e.g. plugin-bookmarks contributes
    "Add bookmark").

  req F-3.1:
    when: plugin is activated
    then: |
      three picker-only actions are contributed — Person, Organization, and
      Note — each matching `http(s)://*/*`, using the extension-bundled
      `snapshot` extractor, and targeting the corresponding
      AddPersonFromSnapshot / AddOrganizationFromSnapshot /
      AddNoteFromSnapshot operation.

  req F-3.2:
    when: the extension lists actions
    then: |
      contributions are resolved per-request, so actions from
      late-activating plugins are included.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Registry Listing

  req F-4.1:
    when: plugin is activated
    then: |
      window event listeners for `composer:page-actions:list` and
      `composer:page-action:invoke` are installed, and a
      `composer:page-actions:ready` event is dispatched so the extension
      relay can refresh its registry even when Composer boots after the
      content script has already installed.

  req F-4.2:
    when: a valid list request arrives
    then: |
      the ack carries the currently contributed actions as serializable
      descriptors, with `operation` serialized to the operation's key string.

  req F-4.3:
    when: a list request fails schema decoding
    then: |
      the ack is { ok: false, error: 'invalidPayload' } with a best-effort
      echo of the request id so the extension can correlate the failure.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Invoke Validation & Dispatch

  req F-5.1:
    when: an invoke request's envelope fails decoding
    then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'invalidPayload' } and nothing is invoked

  req F-5.2:
    when: the envelope has a version other than 1
    then: |
      ack is { ok: false, error: 'unsupportedVersion' } with the request id
      echoed when present.

  req F-5.3:
    when: the strict payload fails decoding
    then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'invalidPayload' }

  req F-5.4:
    when: `actionId` matches no registered action
    then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'unknownAction' }

  req F-5.5:
    when: the active space cannot be determined
    then: nothing is invoked; ack is { ok: false, error: 'noSpace' }

  req F-5.6:
    when: the request resolves to an action and an active space
    then: |
      the action's operation is invoked with
      { snapshot: inputs, target: activeSpace.db }; on success the ack is
      { ok: true, objectId } carrying the created object's id.

  req F-5.7:
    when: the operation returns an error or throws
    then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'operationFailed' }
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Snapshot → Object Mapping
  desc: |
    Each contributed operation maps a Snapshot to an ECHO object and adds it
    to the target database via SpaceOperation.AddObject.

  req F-6.1:
    when: AddPersonFromSnapshot is invoked
    then: |
      a Person is created with best-effort fields:
        fullName  ← hints.h1 ?? hints.ogTitle ?? firstLine(selection.text)
        image     ← hints.ogImage
        notes     ← selection.text (truncated to 4000 chars)
        urls      ← [{ label: source.title || source.url, value: source.url }]

  req F-6.2:
    when: AddOrganizationFromSnapshot is invoked
    then: |
      an Organization is created with best-effort fields:
        name        ← hints.ogTitle ?? hints.h1 ?? firstLine(selection.text)
        description ← hints.ogDescription ?? selection.text (truncated)
        image       ← hints.ogImage
        website     ← source.url

  req F-6.3:
    when: AddNoteFromSnapshot is invoked
    then: |
      a Markdown document is created with a small prelude (title, source
      link, timestamp) followed by the selection's rendered text (truncated
      to 50000 chars). The title falls back through
      hints.h1 ?? hints.ogTitle ?? firstLine(selection.text) ?? source.title.

  req F-6.4:
    when: there is no name/title candidate
    then: the object is still created; empty name is acceptable
```

```mdl
feat F-7: User Feedback

  req F-7.1:
    when: an invoke ack is produced with ok = true
    then: a success toast is shown

  req F-7.2:
    when: an invoke ack is produced with ok = false
    then: an error toast is shown naming the stable error code
```

```mdl
feat F-8: Page Actions Registry & Invocation
  desc: |
    Plugins contribute page actions (serializable descriptor + target
    operation) under a plugin-scoped capability. This plugin answers the
    extension's registry-list requests (`composer:page-actions:list`) with
    descriptors and executes invoke requests (`composer:page-action:invoke`)
    by resolving the active space and invoking the target operation with
    `{ snapshot, target }`. Every request is acked with stable error codes
    (invalidPayload, unsupportedVersion, disabled, unknownAction, noSpace,
    operationFailed); outcomes surface as toasts.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Settings atom registered
  given: plugin activated
  then:
    - the Settings capability is available via Capability.get
    - the default atom value is { enabled: true, autoOpenAfterClip: false,
      renderProxyEnabled: true, renderTimeout: 20000, renderActiveTab: false,
      developerMode: false }
```

```mdl
test T-2: Toggling enabled persists
  given: settings surface rendered
  when: user toggles the `enabled` switch off
  then: subsequent reads of the atom observe enabled === false
```

```mdl
test T-3: List request returns descriptors
  given: contributed picker actions (Person, Organization, Note)
  when: handleListEvent receives { version: 1, id: 'r1' }
  then:
    - ack is { ok: true, id: 'r1' }
    - ack.actions contains one descriptor per action with `operation`
      serialized to the operation key string
```

```mdl
test T-4: Invalid list request is rejected
  given: page-actions listeners installed
  when: handleListEvent receives a malformed detail (missing id)
  then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'invalidPayload' }
```

```mdl
test T-5: Valid person invoke creates Person
  given: a registered add-person action and an active space
  when: |
    handleInvokeEvent receives { version: 1, actionId: <add-person>,
    inputs: snapshot } with snapshot.hints.h1 = 'Jane Doe'
  then:
    - a Person is created with fullName = 'Jane Doe'
    - ack is { ok: true, objectId: <non-empty> }
    - a success toast is shown
```

```mdl
test T-6: Organization mapping falls back to og:title
  given: a snapshot with hints.ogTitle = 'DXOS' and hints.h1 undefined
  when: AddOrganizationFromSnapshot is invoked
  then:
    - Organization.name === 'DXOS'
    - Organization.website === source.url
```

```mdl
test T-7: Missing name is allowed
  given: a snapshot with no hints and empty selection text
  when: the add-person action is invoked
  then:
    - a Person is created (empty fullName)
    - ack is { ok: true, objectId: <non-empty> }
```

```mdl
test T-8: Unsupported envelope version
  given: page-actions listeners installed
  when: handleInvokeEvent receives { version: 2, id: 'r2', ... }
  then:
    - nothing is invoked
    - ack is { ok: false, id: 'r2', error: 'unsupportedVersion' }
```

```mdl
test T-9: Invalid invoke payload is rejected
  given: page-actions listeners installed
  when: handleInvokeEvent receives a version-1 detail missing `actionId`
  then:
    - nothing is invoked
    - ack is { ok: false, error: 'invalidPayload' } with the envelope id echoed
```

```mdl
test T-10: Unknown action
  given: no action registered with id 'nope'
  when: handleInvokeEvent receives a valid request with actionId = 'nope'
  then: ack is { ok: false, error: 'unknownAction' }
```

```mdl
test T-11: No active space
  given: the active space cannot be resolved
  when: a valid invoke request arrives
  then:
    - nothing is invoked
    - ack is { ok: false, error: 'noSpace' }
```

```mdl
test T-12: Operation failure
  given: the target operation returns an error (or throws)
  when: a valid invoke request arrives
  then:
    - ack is { ok: false, error: 'operationFailed' }
    - an error toast is shown
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap
    literals?: UnionList
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```
